Coffee Cake with Chocolate Streusel
  --Jessie Damuck
  
Streusel:
1 c chopped walnuts
1 c semisweet chocolate chips
1/2 c packed light brown sugar
2 tsp cinnamon
pinch kosher salt

Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; set aside.

Cake:
1 c (2 sticks) unsalted butter, room temp + more for pan
4 c ap flour + more for pan
2 tsp baking powder
2 tsp baking soda
1/2 tsp kosher salt
2 c sugar
4 large eggs
2 c sour cream
2 tsp vanilla

Preheat oven to 350F. Butter and flour 12c bundt pan, tapping out excess flour. Whisk flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt in medium bowl. Beat sugar and butter until light and fluffy, ~5 min. Add eggs, one at a time, beating to blend and scraping down the sides after each addition. Reduce speed to low and add dry ingredients in 2 additions, alternating with sour cream. Add vanilla and beat just to combine. Transfer half batter to prepared pan; smooth surface. Sprinkle half of streudel evenly over batter. Scrape in remaining batter, smoothing surface, and sprinkle with remaining streusel. Bake until golden brown and a tester inserted into center comes out clean, 70-80 min. Transfer pan to wire rack and let cool in pan for 30 min before inverting onto wire rack. Let cool completely. Cake can be made 3 days ahead; store tightly coverd at room temp.
